to capture emotions.

103
00:05:46,651 --> 00:05:47,920
Metaphor.

104
00:05:49,211 --> 00:05:50,809
When you feel certain emotions,

105
00:05:50,810 --> 00:05:53,281
describe them with a metaphor.

106
00:05:54,291 --> 00:05:55,680
For example,

107
00:05:55,810 --> 00:05:58,600
if one day you meet someone you like,

108
00:05:59,130 --> 00:06:00,730
you feel a gust or a storm

109
00:06:00,731 --> 00:06:03,720
when looking at her.

110
00:06:05,130 --> 00:06:07,650
When those feelings appear again,

111
00:06:07,651 --> 00:06:08,689
you'll know

112
00:06:08,690 --> 00:06:10,040
it's love.

113
00:06:12,810 --> 00:06:15,410
Emotions are fleeting,

114
00:06:15,411 --> 00:06:18,001
but you should at least recognize them.

115
00:06:18,331 --> 00:06:20,049
Otherwise, you'll be a heartless netizen

116
00:06:20,050 --> 00:06:22,560
who's far away from this world
by the internet.

117
00:06:23,570 --> 00:06:25,689
When you feel such emotions,

118
00:06:25,690 --> 00:06:27,530
it doesn't matter
if you can't understand them

119
00:06:27,531 --> 00:06:29,081
or they make no sense,

120
00:06:29,250 --> 00:06:31,560
describe them with a metaphor.

121
00:06:33,771 --> 00:06:36,881
This is your first assignment.

122
00:06:37,891 --> 00:06:39,480
Will you accomplish it?

123
00:06:42,411 --> 00:06:43,841
Are you still going on blind dates?

124
